## Why Current Approaches Fail

::: columns
:::: column

### All-to-All Topology (Traditional)

```
Platform 1 ←→ Platform 2
     ↓ ↖        ↓ ↖
Platform 3 ←→ Platform 4
```

**Problems:**

- O(n²) connections
- 100 nodes = 9,900 connections
- 49.5 MB/s bandwidth
- **Saturates at 10-20 nodes**

::::
:::: column

### HIVE Hierarchical Topology

```
        Company HQ
           ↓
    ┌──────┴──────┐
Platoon 1      Platoon 2
    ↓              ↓
Squads (4)     Squads (4)
    ↓              ↓
Platforms      Platforms
```

**Advantages:**

- O(n log n) complexity
- 100 nodes = ~300 connections
- 100 KB/s bandwidth
- **Scales to 1000+ nodes**

::::
:::

