## Network Constraint Reality

| Environment | Latency | Bandwidth | Loss Rate | Availability |
|-------------|---------|-----------|-----------|--------------|
| **Ethernet (Tactical LAN)** | 1-10ms | 10Mbps-1Gbps | <0.1% | 99% |
| **Starlink (Satellite)** | 500-800ms | 100-200Mbps | 2-5% | 85% (weather) |
| **MANET (Tactical Radio)** | 50-5000ms | 300bps-2Mbps | 20-30% | 75% (contested) |
| **SA 5G (Private Cellular)** | 20-100ms | 50-500Mbps | 1-3% | 90% (coverage) |

**Critical Requirement:** Must work with **all 4 interfaces simultaneously**

- High-priority commands → Low-latency MANET
- Bulk telemetry → High-bandwidth Starlink
- Reliable C2 → Ethernet when available
- Redundant paths → 5G backup

